        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the syrup",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine sugar and water in a saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring until dissolved. Simmer for 5 minutes. Add lemon juice and orange blossom water. Keep warm over very low heat.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the kataifi layer",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 190°C conventional (170°C fan). Separate the kataifi strands well in a large bowl and pour the melted butter over. Work the butter through the strands with your hands until every strand is coated. Butter a 30 × 20 cm tin. Press half the kataifi into an even, compact layer in the base, pack it firmly, about 1.5 cm deep.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and top",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the mozzarella and ricotta together and spread evenly over the kataifi base, pressing to a level layer. Spread the remaining kataifi evenly on top and press down firmly. The kataifi should be compact and level, not loose.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and invert",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the kataifi is deep amber all over, press the top layer; it should be firm and very crisp. Pour the warm syrup evenly over the surface the moment it comes out of the oven. Leave for 2 to 3 minutes to absorb. Place a large board or tray over the tin and invert in one motion. Lift the tin away. The caramelised underside (now the top) should release cleanly. Garnish with ground pistachios if liked. Serve immediately.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
